last_episode_to_air.name: Peace and Riot
last_episode_to_air.overview: Touché Turtle and Dum Dum try to go on vacation.

name: The Hanna-Barbera New Cartoon Series
overview: A package series composed of three segments featuring Wally Gator, Touché Turtle and Dum Dum, and Lippy the Lion & Hardy Har Har.

episodes.name: Droopy Dragon
episodes.overview: Wally Gator leaves the zoo and goes to a millionare hunter's house. The hunter thinks Wally is a dragon, so he chases Wally.

episodes.name: See-Saw
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy wash ashore on a deserted island, only to discover a pirate burying his treasure... a pirate who believes that "dead men tell no tales!"

episodes.name: Whale of a Tale
episodes.overview: Captain Ahab calls on Touché Turtle and Dum Dum to help him catch Moby Dick.

episodes.name: Gator-Napper
episodes.overview: Two bumbling thieves go to the City Zoo to steal a duck-billed platypus. Because they can't read, they end up grabbing Wally Gator instead!

episodes.name: Water-Melon Felon
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy are kicked off a train and hungry. They come across a dog who is guarding watermelons.

episodes.name: Zero Hero
episodes.overview: Touché Turtle and his sidekick Dum Dum chase a giant gorilla.

episodes.name: Swamp Fever
episodes.overview: Wally's loneliness at the zoo inspires Mr. Twiddles to find him a companion. In the Florida Everglades, he discovers a very traditional Southern gator who comes with a rather "bully" attitude!

episodes.name: Scare to Spare
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy goes in a castle and they meet a mad scientist who created a big, white monster that chases them off.

episodes.name: Dilly of a Lilly
episodes.overview: Touché Turtle and his simple-minded assistant Dum Dum come to the rescue after a cannibal plant escapes from a science lab and wrecks havoc in the town.

episodes.name: White Tie and Frails
episodes.overview: Wally leaves the zoo again, this time he goes to a costume party and a woman wants to dance with him and her boyfriend chases him off.

episodes.name: Gulp and Saucer
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy go on a picnic. They encounters ants who are from outer space that try to steal Lippy and Hardy's picnic food.

episodes.name: Missing Missile
episodes.overview: The military tests a new weapon, a "thinking man's missile." This armament acts with a mind of its own, creating havoc and panic.

episodes.name: Escape Artist
episodes.overview: Wally's the best escape artist at the zoo. Mr. Twiddles the zookeeper is determined to end Wally's wayward ways and hires sleepy-eyed watchdog Snoozer to keep an eye on Wally. Wally's creative efforts to escape from the zoo and spend a night on the town are thwarted by the watchdog.

episodes.name: Map Happy
episodes.overview: On a raft at sea, Lippy and Hardy try to find treasure and deal with a shark.

episodes.name: Lake Serpent
episodes.overview: Touché Turtle and his sidekick Dum Dum chase a green monster.

episodes.name: California or Bust
episodes.overview: When wintertime approaches, Wally plans to go to California and escapes the zoo in a box, but he falls out of a truck and meets a old traveler in the desert who goes after him mistaking him for a Gila monster.

episodes.name: Smile the Wild
episodes.overview: Hardy replaces a missing wild caveman in a circus act. Lippy then trains Hardy for the big top.

episodes.name: You Bug Me
episodes.overview: Touché Turtle battles a large bug in his garden.

episodes.name: Frame and Fortune
episodes.overview: Wally escapes from the zoo and finds a bag of money and tries to get rid of it.

episodes.name: Charge of the Fright Brigade
episodes.overview: While camping out, The duo are mistaken for a red army by a blue army who are playing war games.

episodes.name: Roll-A-Ghoster
episodes.overview: Touché Turtle and Dum-Dum go to Murky Manor to get rid of a wacky ghost.

episodes.name: Tantalizin' Turnips
episodes.overview: Wally escapes from the zoo and rides atop a bus bound for his home near the Everglades. There, he feasts on swamp turnips, much to the irritation of an old nemesis, gun-toting local farmer Swampy Waters.

episodes.name: Film Flam
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy visit Hollywood with the idea of making Lippy a star. He becomes one, all right, with a director who screams for more violence!

episodes.name: Giant Double-Header
episodes.overview: Touché Turtle and Dum Dum go up against a two-headed giant.

episodes.name: Over the Fence Is Out
episodes.overview: Wally kidnaps a mailman and escapes.

episodes.name: Gunflighter
episodes.overview: In order to get food in a town called "Ulch Gulch", Lippy lets Hardy pose as a gunfighter, but things don't go as planned when they meet a real, tough gunfighter.

episodes.name: Loser Take All
episodes.overview: Touché finds himself in a "tortoise and the hare" race, with the prize being the hand of a beautiful princess. There's a surprising finish to this twist on the familiar tale.

episodes.name: Bear with Me
episodes.overview: Mr. Twiddles transfers a polar bear into Wally's cage: a polar bear with a nasty attitude!

episodes.name: Hick Hikers
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy attempt to climb Mount Flooglehorn, the world's tallest mountain, but a mountain goat doesn't even want them to reach the top of it.

episodes.name: Takes Two to Tangle
episodes.overview: Touché and Dum Dum are hired to prevent a bank robbery, only to find out that the thief is a Touché imposter.

episodes.name: Outside Looking In
episodes.overview: Wally tries to break back into the zoo after an evening of heavy partying! Waiting for him is the zoo watchdog!

episodes.name: A Thousand and One Frights
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy come across a arabian who's going to commit sucide because he lost his ruby. Lippy and Hardy find out the ruby is his girlfriend.

episodes.name: Mr. Robots
episodes.overview: An out-of-control robot causes havoc.

episodes.name: Bachelor Buttons
episodes.overview: Mr. Twiddles gets Wally a girlfriend alligator. She turns out to be mean and henpecks Wally mercilessly.

episodes.name: Double Trouble
episodes.overview: Lippy is mistaken for a bank robber.

episodes.name: Touché at Bat
episodes.overview: Touche' and Dum Dum go up against Batface as he tries to swipe the 200 Karat diamond from the Baroness Von Applestrudel.

episodes.name: Which Is Which Witch
episodes.overview: Wally finds himself to be the needed ingredient in a sorceress' brew!

episodes.name: Laugh a Loaf
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy take on the task of making a curmudgeonly old man laugh. He'll pay them $1,000 if they succeed.

episodes.name: Billy the Cad
episodes.overview: Touché and Dum Dum travel to the Old West to go up against a outlaw villain named Billy The Cad.

episodes.name: Pen-Striped Suit
episodes.overview: Wally escapes from the zoo and gets himself in hot water when he wears a pen-striped suit and is mistaken for a criminal.

episodes.name: Genie Is a Meany
episodes.overview: The Genie will grant your wishes- that is, for a price!

episodes.name: Dog Daze
episodes.overview: Touché and Dum Dum helps out a cat with a dog problem (The Dog keeps bullying and treating him like a punching bag).

episodes.name: Ship Shape Escape
episodes.overview: When Wally escapes from the zoo by wearing a boy's sailor suit, he gets mistaken for a navy man by an admiral and finds himself on board a navy ship.

episodes.name: Banks for Everything
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy are out of jobs until Lippy gets an idea. Lippy poses as a housekeeper and Hardy as a baby. They both meet two bank robbers named Little John and Big Jack. They're forced to rob a bank for the thugs.

episodes.name: Ant and Rave
episodes.overview: Touché Turtle and Dum Dum come to the rescue of the Ajax Exterminator Company when their picnic is overrun with ants!

episodes.name: Semi Seminole
episodes.overview: In the Everglades, a young Indian boy is sent out by his father to capture a alligator to prove that he is a brave hunter and the alligator is none other than Wally.

episodes.name: Fiddle Faddled
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy meets a robber who plays a violin to help get things and makes people move.

episodes.name: Black Is the Knigh
episodes.overview: Touché and Dum Dum try to come to the aid of a beautiful princess who has been imprisoned by the Black Knight. It's Touché to the damsel's rescue... until she starts talking about marriage!

episodes.name: Little Red Riding Gator
episodes.overview: Wally wanders from the zoo and finds himself right in the midst of the "Little Red Riding Hood" children's tale. He saves Red Riding Hood from the wolf. This cartoon's many humorous lines include a topical comment by Wally about how there's too much violence on television.

episodes.name: Kidnap Trap
episodes.overview: Lippy dresses Hardy up as a baby and send him in a woman's house to get food.

episodes.name: Dragon Along
episodes.overview: Touché is called to deal with a mischievous dragon who is annoying the king with his fire-breathing antics.

episodes.name: Ice Cube Boob
episodes.overview: Wally escapes the zoo to go to Paris, but winds up at the North Pole when he is thrown out from a plane in a cargo cage and becomes frozen. A German Professor finds him and mistakes him for a prehistoric monster.

episodes.name: Witch Crafty
episodes.overview: A witch turns a prince into a homely hyena. Lippy and Hardy meets the witch who mistakes Hardy for the prince. Everything is all right until the witch, the king, the prince and Lippy all turn into hyenas that look like Hardy.

episodes.name: Satellite Fright
episodes.overview: Touché Turtle and Dum Dum are called upon to guard a supply of anti-gravity pills. Things get wild when a spy sets his eyes upon the goods.

episodes.name: The Forest's Prime Evil
episodes.overview: Wally escapes the zoo and winds up in the forest's prime evil where he meets a Jungle boy who protects the animals.

episodes.name: Gas Again
episodes.overview: Lippy uses laughing gas on Hardy in order to get him to laugh. When a gorilla escapes from a nearby circus, the laughing gas really comes in handy.

episodes.name: Sheepy-Time Pal
episodes.overview: Touché and Dum-Dum are called upon to help a rancher whose sheep are being swiped by a hungry (and clever) wolf.

episodes.name: Snooper Snowzer
episodes.overview: Wally escapes from the zoo to experience a swinging Saturday night in the town. Mr. Twiddles dispatches Snoozer, the alligator watchdog, to use all means necessary to fetch Wally.

episodes.name: Horse and Waggin
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy arrive at a ghost town and sees the only resident there is a ghost horse (who sounds like Mr. Jinks).

episodes.name: Hex Marks the Spot
episodes.overview: A sorcerer shrinks a king and he takes over the castle; Touché and Dum Dum try to get the sorcerer out the castle.

episodes.name: Unconscious Conscience
episodes.overview: Wally finds out that he has a good conscience and a bad conscience; The bad conscience causes him trouble while the good conscience keeps trying to warn him and keep him out of trouble.

episodes.name: Baby Bottled
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy land on a beanstalk and they encounter a giant's baby.

episodes.name: Catch as Cat Can
episodes.overview: Touché Turtle and Dum Dum come to the rescue when a mouse is picked on by a bullying cat.

episodes.name: Gator-Baiter
episodes.overview: Wally orders and builds a robot duplicate of himself from the mail and the robot duplicate creates trouble for him.

episodes.name: Hard Luck Hardy
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy join the Bungling Brothers' Circus, with Hardy becoming "Fearless Hardy, the World's Greatest Lion Tamer."

episodes.name: Sea for Two
episodes.overview: Touché and Dum Dum are challenged to a duel by the notorious pirate Jolly Roger.

episodes.name: False Alarm
episodes.overview: A bird makes a sound to warn Mr. Twiddle. "Fweep, Fweep, Fweep, fweep!" Most of the cartoon has Wally attempting to silence the bird. Every time Wally attempts escape the bird sounds the alarm.

episodes.name: Snow Use
episodes.overview: Ice fishers Lippy and Hardy deals and meets a fish-loving penguin and pesters them and keeps taking their fishes.

episodes.name: High Goon
episodes.overview: Loco Weed Willie, a western outlaw, plans to get even with Touché when he gets out of jail.

episodes.name: Phantom Alligator
episodes.overview: Wally escapes the zoo by using a jackhammer and hides out at a wealthy woman's mansion and scares her and her butler.

episodes.name: Injun Trouble
episodes.overview: In the west, Lippy and Hardy are potion sellers and they meet a Indian chief who demands them to make his chubby Indian daughter beautiful with a potion.

episodes.name: Grandma Outlaw
episodes.overview: Touché Turtle and Dum Dum must stop a bank robber masquerading as a grandmother.

episodes.name: Puddle Hopper
episodes.overview: Wally wants to give Mr. Twiddles' new scooter a try. His efforts lead to riotous chaos and havoc at the zoo!

episodes.name: Mouse in the House
episodes.overview: A man hires mouse exterminators Lippy and Hardy to get rid of a mouse at his home.

episodes.name: Duel Control
episodes.overview: Touché takes the Masked Avenger's place when he injures his leg to give money back to the poor from a money collector.

episodes.name: Baby Chase
episodes.overview: A tired delivery stork delivers a baby gorilla to the wrong zoo and the baby gorilla lands on Wally and the baby gorilla aggressively plays with him.

episodes.name: Crazy Cat Capers
episodes.overview: Lippy becomes a woman's pet and is brought to her home, then her hunter husband meets and tries to blast him.

episodes.name: Rapid Rabbit
episodes.overview: Touché Turtle and Dum Dum go up against a speed-moving, carrot-stealing rabbit who is raiding a farmer's garden.

episodes.name: Gosh Zilla
episodes.overview: Mr. Twiddle gives Wally some vitamin pills, but the pills actually make Wally grow to hundreds of feet tall! Wandering around town, Wally is taken for a prehistoric monster. Due to his resemblance to famous movie monsters, a Hollywood director is soon chasing after Wally with cameras!

episodes.name: Phoney Pony
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy are part of a costumed "horse" act on TV. Their misfortune leads them into a robbery, a horse race, and a chase by the cops.

episodes.name: Thumb Hero
episodes.overview: Touché Turtle and Dum Dum are called upon to solve a string of jewelry store robberies. All the evidence points to Tom Thumb! Or could it be Tom Crumb?

episodes.name: Camera Shy Guy
episodes.overview: Wally wanders from the zoo to get discover and stars in a jungle picture and gets thrashed around by a method actor in his part.

episodes.name: Egg Experts
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy want to eat a egg but a fox (who speaks like Groucho Marx) also wants it.

episodes.name: Kat-Napped
episodes.overview: A desperate canary asks for Touché's help in fending off a vicious cat. Touché's creative solution adds the perfect touch.

episodes.name: Rebel Rabble
episodes.overview: During springtime, Wally heads back to the Everglades where he meets a pretty southern lady alligator and the tough, southern gator (from the episode "Swamp Fever") and they vie to see who will court her.

episodes.name: Rabbit Romeo
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy meets a heartbroken rabbit who was dumped by his girlfriend.

episodes.name: Romeo, Touché, and Juliet
episodes.overview: William Shakespeare's classic tale gets a "mod" twist, with Romeo seeking Touché Turtle's help in getting Juliet's affections.

episodes.name: No More Mower
episodes.overview: Mr. Twiddle buys a new power mower and Wally pulls the lever on the handle and he accidentally takes off with it.

episodes.name: Bird in the Hand
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy take on the task of finding an extinct dodo bird on a faraway island. The dodo that they find exceeds all their expectations.

episodes.name: The Big Bite
episodes.overview: A mad scientist creates a giant mosquito, and it's up to Touché Turtle to do something about it. He battles the big skeeter, and his solution for victory provides a surprising conclusion.

episodes.name: Knight Nut
episodes.overview: A German scientist kidnaps Wally and takes him to his laboratory and sends him back in time to the middle ages where a knight mistakes him for a dragon he was going after.

episodes.name: Legion Heirs
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy are drafted as legion beaus to rescue the admiral's daughter from a very politically incorrect sheik.

episodes.name: Flying Saucer Sorcerer
episodes.overview: Touché and Dum Dum investigate a spaceship landing on Earth when a little Martian comes out and wants to explore the city, but he uses Touché's body to walk around.

episodes.name: Ape Scrape
episodes.overview: One of the zoo's apes looks to Wally for advice on how to escape. Wally's teachings create disaster at every turn.

episodes.name: Hoots and Saddles
episodes.overview: Lippy enters Hardy in Mild Bill's Rodeo to ride Blast Off, a wild, bronco-busting rodeo horse for 10 seconds to win $1,000 dollars, but Hardy rides off with Blast Off and Lippy tries to stop and bring them back to the rodeo.

episodes.name: Aladdin's Lampoon
episodes.overview: Touché Turtle and Dum Dum help a young Aladdin.

episodes.name: Gator-Imitator
episodes.overview: A crook, Lefty Wright escapes from prison and dons an alligator costume, causing all kinds of problems for Wally.

episodes.name: Monster Mix-Up
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy take on the job of babysitting a young boy. This juvenile has his own laboratory in which he creates a secret potion- a potion that when drunk...

episodes.name: Haunting License
episodes.overview: Touché Turtle and Dum Dum are asked by a man who is about to inherit a castle to see if is haunted when a sword that comes to live pokes him and chases him out, but later they find out a realtor is behind the haunted sword bit.

episodes.name: Safe at Home
episodes.overview: Wally signs up to be on a baseball team called "The Florida Gators" when a baseball scout sees him throwing a rock at a father.

episodes.name: Bye-Bye Fly-Guy
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy stowaway on a plane when the pilot leaves them and they get stuck flying the plane.

episodes.name: The Phoney Phantom
episodes.overview: A fox disguises himself and takes eggs from a hen and the farmer calls Touché and Dum Dum to see about the situation.

episodes.name: Balloon Buffoon
episodes.overview: Twiddle lets Wally out of his cage on the Honor System. Of course, Wally tries to escape- this time he buys a batch of helium balloons and floats away! Following a few airborne misadventures, the Air Force is called out to confront the UFO.

episodes.name: Wooden Nickels
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy get money from a dog to eat out until they realize the money is from a counterfeiter.

episodes.name: Touché's Last Stand
episodes.overview: General George Custard is surrounded by Indians in the famous battle and he calls for Touche' Turtle.

episodes.name: Rassle Dazzle
episodes.overview: Wally signs up for a membership to a gym, and winds up in a professional wrestling match instead. His opponent is a Japanese Black Belt named Tokyo Rosa.

episodes.name: Two for the Road
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy compete against a man to drive trucks across the country.

episodes.name: Chief Beef
episodes.overview: Captain John Smith gets into a bad situation with an indian, so he calls Touche' Turtle to the rescue.

episodes.name: Sea Sick Pals
episodes.overview: When Mr. Twiddle goes on a vacation cruise, Wally gets locked in Twiddles' trunk by the moving man and winds up on the cruise with him for a brief while.

episodes.name: King's X
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy find themselves cast adrift on a faraway island, only to find Lippy greeted as the island's new king. Then he has to deal with a King Kong-type menace pestering the natives.

episodes.name: Like Wild, Man
episodes.overview: Touché comes to the aid of Robinson Crusoe, who's having problems with a most "wild" Man Friday! Crusoe utters lots of 1960s "hip" and "mod" language.

episodes.name: Accidentally on Purpose
episodes.overview: An insurance salesman tries to get Wally to buy. When accidents begin to happen, Wally reconsiders.

episodes.name: Amusement Park Lark
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy breaks into a amusement park.

episodes.name: Dum de Dum Dum
episodes.overview: Dum Dum is kidnapped by the dogcatcher, and Touché needs to rescue him.

episodes.name: Whistle Stopper
episodes.overview: Mr. Twiddle makes a whistle and it's too much for Wally to handle.

episodes.name: T for Two
episodes.overview: At a golf course, Lippy and Hardy are mistaken for caddies.

episodes.name: Et Tu Touché?
episodes.overview: In Rome, Touché and Dum Dum helps out a emperor being picked on by would-be emperors.

episodes.name: Birthday Grievings
episodes.overview: On Wally's birthday, he and Mr. Twiddle remember the times of Wally's childhood birthdays at the zoo and how he got Twiddle in all kinds of trouble.

episodes.name: Tiny Troubles
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy are stranded on the island of Lilliput where they are embroiled in the feuding of Lilliput and Silliput.

episodes.name: Dragon Feat
episodes.overview: Touché Turtle and Dum Dum have problems trying to bring a fire-breathing dragon to go to a bratty young prince's birthday.

episodes.name: Medicine Avenue
episodes.overview: Wally fakes being sick so he can take an ambulance out of the zoo, only to find himself in the hands of a crazy doctor (complete with German accent!) performing all sorts of painful tests.

episodes.name: Flood for a Thought
episodes.overview: When the duo are put out off a bus in the middle of the desert, they wander over to Green Acres, where there is nothing green about it and they encounter a rancher who needs and wants rain, so Lippy and Hardy attempts to make it rain.

episodes.name: Red Riding Hoodlum
episodes.overview: Touché and Dum Dum are asked by Red Riding Hood to take her basket full of goodies to her grandmother's house and protect her from the wolf.

episodes.name: Marshall Wally
episodes.overview: Our hero gets a visit from his fairy godmother. Wally wishes to become a Western lawman!

episodes.name: Hocus Focus
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy take jobs as camera men for "Strife Magazine" to snap a good picture, but they encounter a diamond thief and have trouble dealing with him.

episodes.name: Dough Nuts
episodes.overview: Touché Turtle and Dum Dum are up against a mad scientist and his robot.

episodes.name: One Round Trip
episodes.overview: Wally flees the zoo by using a inner-tube and his getaway in a baby carriage and rides off to a space shuttle where he gets blasted off in a rocket to a strange planet where two martians volunteer him to test their new experimental rocket and meets their leader who looks just like Wally himself.

episodes.name: Shamrocked
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy have a encounter with a leprechaun who's looking for a pot of gold.

episodes.name: Save the Last Trance for Me
episodes.overview: Villain Hypno-Harry plans to use hypnosis to make Touché Turtle his partner in crime. Their first heist: the Brooklyn Bridge. Next: the Empire State Building!

episodes.name: Gopher Broke
episodes.overview: Wally battles with a pesky gopher at at the zoo.

episodes.name: Old Fuddy Duds
episodes.overview: The duo get jobs as bodyguards for Old Man Rivers, a eccentric, wealthy old rancher who is in a wheelchair and fires his guns.

episodes.name: Waterloo for Two
episodes.overview: Napoleon calls for Touché Turtle during the historic battle with Wellington.

episodes.name: Gladiator Gator
episodes.overview: Wally takes a turn at joining the circus, only to find out that he's destined for a fight with a boxing kangaroo. Killer Kangaroo's previous opponents, a "ferocious" tiger, lion and ape, have been crossed off the fight card.

episodes.name: Chow You Feelings
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy go to an island and meet a Robinson Crusoe-like islander.

episodes.name: Robin Hoodlum
episodes.overview: Robin Hood asks Touché to fill in for him in Sherwood Forest while he goes on vacation. Needless to say, things don't go quite as planned.

episodes.name: Bubble Trouble
episodes.overview: A nearby farmer mistakes Wally for a space alien when Wally drifts by in a giant bubble.

episodes.name: Easy Doesn't It
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy are wandering in the desert when they encounter an old mine. They have to deal with the mine's watchdog and a bottle of nitroglycerine!

episodes.name: The Shoe Must Go On
episodes.overview: Touché Turtle and Dum Dum's new job is trying to help an old lady who lives in a shoe find her and her children another giant shoe for room and space; They go up a beanstalk and try to get one from a giant.

episodes.name: Ice Charades
episodes.overview: Wally decides to take up ice skating and finds himself smack dab in the middle of an ice show (with Mr. Twiddles).

episodes.name: Drop Me a Lion
episodes.overview: A man at a hospital wants Lippy and Hardy to do him a favor. He wants them to bring something to a gangster.

episodes.name: Quack Hero
episodes.overview: A new superhero called Dynamic Duck, cuts in on Touché's hero work and Touche feels he is no longer needed when there's danger, so he retires and Dum Dum joins Dynamic Duck.

episodes.name: Creature Feature
episodes.overview: Wally tries to sneak into a downtown science fiction/horror movie show, "The Creature From Planet Nix." Needless to say, things don't go quite as planned.

episodes.name: Map Sap
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy get a tip on some buried pirate treasure. It's buried under a city jail, so they do all that they can to get themselves arrested. Amusing moments abound as cartoon "heroes" set bad examples.

episodes.name: Aliblabber and the Forty Thieves
episodes.overview: Aliblabber sends for Touche to help him catch Ama Hoodlum and his thieves who are holed up in a cave.

episodes.name: Squatter's Rights
episodes.overview: Wally goes to a island and meets a short man there.

episodes.name: Shark Shock
episodes.overview: Lippy takes a job as a lifeguard at a beach. His first encounter is with a shark who's escaped from a nearby water act!

episodes.name: Out of This Whirl
episodes.overview: Touché and Dum Dum helps a TV radio broadcaster when he sees a martian flying in on his broadcast.

episodes.name: The Big Drip
episodes.overview: When a drippy pipe bothers Wally, he tries to fix it without calling a plumber to come by, but he makes things worse when he causes a major flood at the zoo.

episodes.name: No Spooking Allowed
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy are stagecoach drivers who have a rather frantic tussle with the Western outlaw The Ghost Rider.

episodes.name: Hero on the Half Shell
episodes.overview: Touché's young nephew, Teensy Turtle, comes to spend the weekend with him and Dum Dum, but while he spends the weekend with his uncle, Teensy wants to help Touché catch a escaped convict named "Moose".

episodes.name: Gourmet Gator
episodes.overview: Wally is tired of eating swamp grass at the zoo. He escapes to the classiest restaurant in town, only to run into a Russian chef with a temper (and some knives).

episodes.name: Me-My-Mine
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy buy a map to the Lost Dutchman Mine from a Native American salesman. Lippy and Hardy have struck it rich... or so they think!

episodes.name: Tenderfoot Turtle
episodes.overview: Touché and Dum Dum takes charge of a boy scout group in the forest.

episodes.name: Carpet Bragger
episodes.overview: A Southern alligator named Col. Zachary Gator makes his way to Wally's zoo. He tries everything to get rid of Wally in order to take his place.

episodes.name: Together Mess
episodes.overview: Lippy and Hardy become handcuffed together and try different ways to get the handcuffs off.

episodes.name: Peace and Riot
episodes.overview: Touché Turtle and Dum Dum try to go on vacation.
